# 🧨 Kubernetes Deletion Commands – Cheat Sheet

---

## 🔹 1. Delete a **Pod**

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name> -n <namespace>
```

Force delete (stuck pod):

```bash
kubectl delete pod <pod-name> -n <namespace> --grace-period=0 --force
```

Delete all pods with a label:

```bash
kubectl delete pod -n job-scheduler -l app=job-service
```

---

## 🔹 2. Delete a **Deployment**

```bash
kubectl delete deployment <deployment-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete deployment job-service -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 3. Delete a **StatefulSet** (Kafka, DBs, Loki)

```bash
kubectl delete statefulset <name> -n <namespace>
```

⚠️ Pods will be deleted, **PVCs stay unless removed manually**

---

## 🔹 4. Delete a **Service**

```bash
kubectl delete service <service-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete svc job-consumer-nodeport -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 5. Delete a **ConfigMap**

```bash
kubectl delete configmap <configmap-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete cm job-service-config -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 6. Delete a **Secret**

```bash
kubectl delete secret <secret-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete secret db-credentials -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 7. Delete a **PVC (PersistentVolumeClaim)**

```bash
kubectl delete pvc <pvc-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete pvc jobservice-pvc -n job-scheduler
```

🔴 **Data loss warning** – volume data will be gone (unless Retain policy)

---

## 🔹 8. Delete a **PersistentVolume (PV)**

```bash
kubectl delete pv <pv-name>
```

List PVs:

```bash
kubectl get pv
```

---

## 🔹 9. Delete an **HPA**

```bash
kubectl delete hpa <hpa-name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete hpa job-service-hpa -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 10. Delete a **DaemonSet** (Promtail)

```bash
kubectl delete daemonset <name> -n <namespace>
```

Example:

```bash
kubectl delete daemonset promtail -n monitoring
```

---

## 🔹 11. Delete an **Ingress**

```bash
kubectl delete ingress <ingress-name> -n <namespace>
```

---

## 🔹 12. Delete **RBAC Resources**

ServiceAccount:

```bash
kubectl delete sa promtail -n job-scheduler
```

ClusterRole:

```bash
kubectl delete clusterrole promtail
```

ClusterRoleBinding:

```bash
kubectl delete clusterrolebinding promtail
```

---

## 🔹 13. Delete an Entire **Namespace** (🔥 Nuclear Option)

```bash
kubectl delete namespace job-scheduler
```

⚠️ Deletes **everything inside**:

* Pods
* Services
* Deployments
* PVCs
* ConfigMaps
* Secrets

---

## 🔹 14. Delete Resources Using YAML File

```bash
kubectl delete -f deployment.yaml
```

Multiple files:

```bash
kubectl delete -f .
```

---

## 🔹 15. Bulk Delete by Resource Type

Delete all deployments:

```bash
kubectl delete deployment --all -n job-scheduler
```

Delete all services:

```bash
kubectl delete svc --all -n job-scheduler
```

Delete everything except PVCs:

```bash
kubectl delete all --all -n job-scheduler
```

---

## 🔹 16. Cleanup Stuck / Terminating Resources

Remove finalizers:

```bash
kubectl patch <resource> <name> -n <namespace> \
-p '{"metadata":{"finalizers":null}}' --type=merge
```

---

# ✅ Common Safe Cleanup Order (Recommended)

```text
1. HPA
2. Ingress
3. Services
4. Deployments / StatefulSets
5. DaemonSets
6. ConfigMaps / Secrets
7. PVCs
8. Namespace (if needed)
```

