# 🧹 1️⃣ SAFE CLEANUP SCRIPT (Job Scheduler Stack)

This script **cleans everything safely** without breaking the cluster.

### 📌 What it deletes

* Deployments
* StatefulSets
* Services
* HPAs
* DaemonSets
* ConfigMaps
* Secrets
* (Optionally) PVCs

---

### 🔹 `cleanup-job-scheduler.sh`

```bash
#!/bin/bash

NAMESPACE=job-scheduler

echo "🔴 Cleaning namespace: $NAMESPACE"

echo "▶ Deleting HPAs"
kubectl delete hpa --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting Services"
kubectl delete svc --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting Deployments"
kubectl delete deploy --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting StatefulSets"
kubectl delete sts --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting DaemonSets"
kubectl delete ds --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting ConfigMaps"
kubectl delete cm --all -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "▶ Deleting Secrets (except default)"
kubectl get secrets -n $NAMESPACE \
  | grep -v default-token \
  | awk '{print $1}' \
  | xargs kubectl delete secret -n $NAMESPACE --ignore-not-found

echo "✅ Cleanup completed (PVCs not deleted)"
```

Make executable:

```bash
chmod +x cleanup-job-scheduler.sh
```

Run:

```bash
./cleanup-job-scheduler.sh
```

